{0 Middle-end}

The middle-end builds semantic proof data from the source program:

- automata generation from assumptions/guarantees;
- product construction between program transitions and automata transitions;
- canonical contract construction;
- pre/invariant/post passes;
- proof-view extraction.

{1 Scope}

This layer is where Kairos turns parsed nodes into canonical proof obligations.
It does not emit Why3 text directly; that is handled by backend layers.

{1 Main areas in the repository}

- `lib/domain/middleend/automata/spec`
  Specification automata generation.

- `lib/domain/middleend/automata/product`
  Product construction and transition classification.

- `lib/domain/middleend/ir`
  Canonical IR shaping passes (`pre`, `invariant`, `post`) and proof views.

{1 Reading order}

1. automata generation (`automata/spec`)
2. product build (`automata/product`)
3. IR passes (`ir`)
